SAFETY_001.text: Do you have any of these symptoms that need immediate medical attention?

options.text: Numbness in groin/buttocks area or loss of bladder/bowel control
Severe weakness in both legs or spreading numbness
Chest pain, severe shortness of breath, or heart palpitations

SAFETY_002.text: Have you experienced any unexplained weight loss, fever, or night sweats recently?

SAFETY_003.text: Have you had a recent significant trauma, fall, or accident?

options.text: Woke up with it one morning

CONTEXT_002.text: How long have you had this problem?

CONTEXT_003.text: On a scale of 0-10, how severe is your pain at its worst?

REGION_001.text: What is your main problem area?

SHOULDER_001.text: Do you have sharp pain when reaching overhead?

SHOULDER_002.text: Does pain wake you up at night when lying on that shoulder?

SHOULDER_003.text: Are you gradually losing range of motion in your shoulder?

SHOULDER_004.text: Is your shoulder stiff, especially in the morning?

SHOULDER_005.text: Do you have a painful arc of motion between 60-120 degrees?

SHOULDER_006.text: Do you feel weakness when lifting your arm?

SHOULDER_007.text: Does your pain improve after a few minutes of movement (warming up)?

SHOULDER_008.text: Do you feel clicking or catching in your shoulder?

SHOULDER_009.text: Is your pain mainly at the front of your shoulder?

SHOULDER_010.text: Did you hear or feel a pop when the injury occurred?

ELBOW_001.text: Is your pain on the outside of your elbow?

ELBOW_002.text: Is your pain on the inside of your elbow?

ELBOW_003.text: Does gripping objects or shaking hands cause pain?

ELBOW_004.text: Does pain occur when you extend your wrist against resistance?

ELBOW_005.text: Do you have numbness or tingling in your ring and little fingers?

ELBOW_006.text: Are your symptoms worse when your elbow is bent for long periods?

WRIST_001.text: Do you have numbness or tingling in your thumb, index, or middle fingers?

WRIST_002.text: Are your symptoms worse at night or wake you from sleep?

WRIST_003.text: Is your pain on the thumb side of your wrist?

WRIST_004.text: Does moving your thumb or making a fist cause pain?

WRIST_005.text: Does one of your fingers catch or lock when bending?

WRIST_006.text: Can you feel a nodule or bump in your palm?

KNEE_001.text: Does your knee give way or feel unstable?

KNEE_002.text: Do you have catching or locking sensations in your knee?

KNEE_003.text: Did your knee swell rapidly after the injury?

KNEE_004.text: Did you hear or feel a pop when the injury occurred?

KNEE_005.text: Is your pain at the front of your knee around the kneecap?

KNEE_006.text: Is your pain worse going up or down stairs?

KNEE_007.text: Do you feel grinding or crepitus when moving your knee?

KNEE_008.text: Is your pain on the outside of your knee?

KNEE_009.text: Is your pain worse when running, especially at a certain distance?

KNEE_010.text: Is your pain on the inside of your knee?

KNEE_011.text: Is your pain just below your kneecap at the patellar tendon?

KNEE_012.text: Is your pain worse with jumping activities?

ANKLE_001.text: Is your pain on the outside of your ankle?

ANKLE_002.text: Did you roll your ankle inward (inversion injury)?

ANKLE_003.text: Does your ankle frequently give way or feel unstable?

ANKLE_004.text: Is your pain at the back of your heel/Achilles area?

ANKLE_005.text: Is your pain worse when you first start moving but improves with activity?

ANKLE_006.text: Is your pain on the inside of your ankle?

ANKLE_007.text: Did you twist your ankle outward (external rotation)?

ANKLE_008.text: Is your pain above the ankle joint (between shin and ankle)?

FOOT_001.text: Is your pain at the bottom of your heel?

FOOT_002.text: Is your pain worst with the first steps in the morning?

FOOT_003.text: Is your pain in the ball of your foot (forefoot)?

FOOT_004.text: Do you have burning, tingling, or numbness in your toes?

FOOT_005.text: Is your pain worse when wearing tight shoes?

FOOT_006.text: Is your arch collapsing or becoming flatter?

LUMBAR_001.text: Does your pain radiate down your leg below the knee?

LUMBAR_002.text: Do you have numbness or tingling in your leg?

LUMBAR_003.text: Is your pain worse when sitting?

LUMBAR_004.text: Is your pain worse when bending forward?

LUMBAR_005.text: Is your pain worse when walking but relieved by sitting?

LUMBAR_006.text: Does leaning forward or bending at the waist relieve your symptoms?

LUMBAR_007.text: Is your pain worse when arching your back backward?

LUMBAR_008.text: Is your pain mainly in your buttock?

LUMBAR_009.text: Is your pain predominantly on one side?

CERVICAL_001.text: Does your pain radiate down your arm?

CERVICAL_002.text: Do you have numbness or tingling in your arm or hand?

CERVICAL_003.text: Is your head tilted to one side and difficult to straighten?

CERVICAL_004.text: Were you in a car accident or had a whiplash-type injury?

CERVICAL_005.text: Do you have headaches that start from your neck?

CERVICAL_006.text: Are your symptoms worse when holding your arms overhead?

HIP_001.text: Is your pain in your groin area?

HIP_002.text: Is your pain on the outside of your hip?

HIP_003.text: Is your pain worse when lying on the affected side?

HIP_004.text: Do you feel clicking or catching in your hip?

HIP_005.text: Is your pain worse with deep hip flexion (like bringing knee to chest)?

HIP_006.text: Is your hip stiff, especially in the morning?

THORACIC_001.text: Is your pain in the chest wall area?

THORACIC_002.text: Can you reproduce the pain by pressing on your ribs?

THORACIC_003.text: Is your pain worse with deep breathing?

THORACIC_004.text: Do you notice a visible curve in your spine?

HEAD_001.text: Do you have jaw pain or clicking?

HEAD_003.text: Are your vertigo episodes brief (less than 1 minute)?

HEAD_004.text: Is your vertigo triggered by head movements (like looking up or rolling over)?

SYSTEMIC_001.text: Do you have widespread pain in multiple areas of your body?

SYSTEMIC_003.text: Is your morning stiffness lasting more than 60 minutes?

SYSTEMIC_004.text: Are your joint symptoms symmetric (affecting both sides equally)?

SYSTEMIC_005.text: Do you have trouble sleeping or unrefreshing sleep?

NEURO_001.text: Do you have problems with balance or coordination?

NEURO_002.text: Do you have a tremor, especially when your hands are at rest?

NEURO_003.text: Have your movements become slower than before?

NEURO_005.text: Are your symptoms only on one side of your body?

NEURO_006.text: Do your symptoms come and go (relapsing and remitting)?

NEURO_007.text: Have you noticed any vision problems?

GENERAL_PAIN_001.text: Is your pain worse at night?

GENERAL_PAIN_002.text: Does your pain improve with rest?

GENERAL_PAIN_003.text: Have you had similar episodes before?

PELVIS_001.text: Is your pain in the pubic area or lower abdomen?

PELVIS_002.text: Do you have pain in your buttock that radiates down your leg?

PELVIS_003.text: Is your pain related to your menstrual cycle?

PELVIS_004.text: Do you have pain or difficulty with urination?

PELVIS_005.text: Do you feel heaviness or pressure in your pelvic area?

PELVIS_006.text: Is your pain worse when sitting for long periods?

LOWER_LEG_001.text: Is your pain in your calf muscle?

LOWER_LEG_002.text: Is your pain along the front of your shin?

LOWER_LEG_003.text: Did your pain start during running or exercise?

LOWER_LEG_004.text: Do you have cramping or tightness in your calf during walking?

LOWER_LEG_005.text: Is there swelling, redness, or warmth in your calf?

LOWER_LEG_006.text: Does your pain get worse with activity and improve with rest?

CARDIO_001.text: Do you get short of breath with activities that didn't used to bother you?

CARDIO_002.text: Do you have a chronic cough or wheeze?

CARDIO_003.text: Do you have swelling in your ankles or legs?

CARDIO_004.text: Have you had a recent heart attack or heart surgery?

CARDIO_005.text: Do you get leg pain when walking that goes away with rest?

CARDIO_006.text: Do you feel unusually tired even after rest?

SHOULDER_011.text: Is your pain on the very top of your shoulder (where shoulder meets collarbone)?

SHOULDER_012.text: Does reaching across your body (like touching opposite shoulder) cause pain?

SHOULDER_013.text: Is your pain worse when lying on the affected shoulder at night?

SHOULDER_014.text: Can you see or feel your shoulder blade sticking out abnormally?

SHOULDER_015.text: Is your pain in your chest/front of shoulder near the armpit?

SHOULDER_016.text: Do you have weakness when pushing (like doing a push-up)?

SHOULDER_017.text: Did your pain come on suddenly and severely?

CERVICAL_007.text: Do your symptoms affect BOTH arms (not just one side)?

CERVICAL_008.text: Have you noticed problems with walking, balance, or coordination?

CERVICAL_009.text: Have you noticed clumsiness with your hands (dropping things, difficulty with buttons)?

CERVICAL_010.text: Is your pain at the back of your head (base of skull)?

CERVICAL_011.text: Do you have shooting or electric shock-like pain?

CERVICAL_012.text: Do you feel grinding or crunching when moving your neck?

CERVICAL_013.text: Has your neck problem lasted more than 3 months?

CERVICAL_014.text: Is your pain just in your neck WITHOUT arm symptoms?

NEURO_008.text: Did your symptoms start in childhood?

NEURO_009.text: Do you have muscle stiffness or spasticity (tight, hard to move)?

NEURO_010.text: Is your weakness getting progressively worse over months?

NEURO_011.text: Do you have involuntary jerky or dance-like movements (chorea)?

NEURO_012.text: Does your weakness get worse with repeated activity and improve with rest?

NEURO_013.text: Do you have drooping eyelids or double vision?

NEURO_014.text: Did your weakness start in your legs and spread upward over days/weeks?

NEURO_016.text: Do you have a tremor mainly when reaching for objects (not at rest)?

NEURO_017.text: Did you have a recent head injury or trauma?

NEURO_018.text: Do you have involuntary sustained muscle contractions causing abnormal postures?

NEURO_019.text: Did you have a spinal cord injury (trauma, accident)?

ELBOW_007.text: Do you have swelling at the back of your elbow (pointy part)?

ELBOW_008.text: Is your pain worse with throwing or overhead sports?

ELBOW_009.text: Is your pain in your forearm (between elbow and wrist)?

ELBOW_010.text: Is your pain worse when rotating your forearm palm-down (pronation)?

ELBOW_011.text: Do you feel grinding or crunching when moving your elbow?

ELBOW_012.text: Do you have difficulty fully straightening your elbow?

ELBOW_013.text: Have you had recent elbow surgery or fracture?

WRIST_007.text: Is the pain on the back (top) of your wrist?

WRIST_008.text: Is the pain on the palm side of your wrist?

WRIST_009.text: Is your pain on the pinky side of your wrist?

WRIST_010.text: Can you see or feel a bump or lump on your wrist?

WRIST_011.text: Can you NOT fully straighten the tip of one of your fingers?

WRIST_012.text: Can you NOT bend/curl the tip of one of your fingers?

WRIST_013.text: Is your pain at the base of your thumb?

WRIST_014.text: Does your thumb feel unstable or give way?

WRIST_015.text: Is one of your fingers progressively curling towards your palm?

WRIST_016.text: Have you had a wrist fracture or been in a cast recently?

WRIST_017.text: Is your pain in the snuffbox area (hollow at base of thumb on back of hand)?

SYSTEMIC_006.text: Do you feel significantly worse after physical or mental exertion (post-exertional malaise)?

SYSTEMIC_007.text: Do you have burning or shooting pain that seems out of proportion to the injury?

SYSTEMIC_008.text: Does even light touch cause pain (allodynia)?

SYSTEMIC_009.text: Do you notice color or temperature changes in the affected limb?

SYSTEMIC_010.text: Are your joints unusually flexible (can you touch your thumb to your forearm)?

SYSTEMIC_011.text: Do you have a history of frequent joint dislocations or sprains?

SYSTEMIC_012.text: Do you have very stretchy or fragile skin that bruises easily?

SYSTEMIC_013.text: Does your back stiffness improve with exercise but worsen with rest?

SYSTEMIC_014.text: Do you have psoriasis (skin condition with red, scaly patches)?

SYSTEMIC_015.text: Do you have swollen, sausage-like fingers or toes (dactylitis)?

SYSTEMIC_016.text: Have you had fractures from minor trauma or noticed you are getting shorter?

FOOT_007.text: Is your big toe drifting towards your other toes with a bony bump on the side?

FOOT_008.text: Is your big toe stiff and painful when you try to bend it upward?

FOOT_009.text: Do you have one or more toes that are permanently bent in a claw-like position?

FOOT_010.text: Are you a child or teenager with heel pain after sports?

FOOT_011.text: Did you injure your big toe by jamming it or bending it back too far?

FOOT_012.text: Is your pain under the ball of your foot at the base of your big toe?

FOOT_013.text: Is your pain on the outer (lateral) side of your midfoot?

FOOT_014.text: Do you have burning, tingling, or numbness on the bottom of your foot?

FOOT_015.text: Did you have a twisting injury and now cannot put weight on your midfoot?

FOOT_016.text: Do you have a flat arch that has developed or gotten worse over time?
